DONALD M. SMITH v. UNION TRUST COMPANY [No. 69,

September Term, 1982.]

Decided July 27, 1982.

The cause was submitted to Murphy, C. J., and Smith, Eldridge, Cole, Davidson, Rodowsky and Couch, JJ.

Per Curiam:

The petition for writ of certiorari having been granted, the case is remanded to the Baltimore City Court without affirmance or reversal, for reconsideration in light of Union Trust Co. v. Tyndall, 290 Md. 102, 428 A.2d 428 (1981).

Judge Davidson would have denied the petition.

Case remanded to the Baltimore City Court for reconsideration.

Costs to abide the result.
